d at reclaiming vacant, contaminated, underutilized and/or under-maintained land and waterways for community benefit. This whats next? agenda is a strong suit of the Groundwork model and, as such, holds great potential for these two cities as well as building the next generation of organizers and social justice leaders while recognizing the key role that the voice of youth has to play in this work alongside of adult and other marginalized residents.</p>\n','Why Fall River and New Bedford','','inherit','closed','closed','','33-revision-v1','','','2017-06-04 15:31:16','2017-06-04 15:31:16','',33,'http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/33-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(316,8,'2017-06-04 15:36:00','2017-06-04 15:36:00','\n	<p>Mission Statement</p>\n<p>Fall River &amp; New Bedford</p>\n<p>History</p>\n<p>Staff &amp; Board</p>\n<p>Our Stories</p>\n	<h2>MISSION STATEMENT</h2>\n<hr />\n<p>The mission of Groundwork Southcoast (GWSC) is to bring about the sustained regeneration, improvement and management of the physical environment by developing community-based partnerships that empower people, businesses and organizations to promote environmental, economic and social well-being.<br />\n&nbsp</p>\n<h2>OUR ROLE</h2>\n<hr />\n<p>GWSC is part of the <a href=\"http://groundworkusa.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Groundwork USA</strong></a> network of independent, not-for-profit, environmental organizations called Groundwork Trusts. Locally organized and controlled, Groundwork Trusts provide services focused on improving their communities environment, economy, and quality of life.</p>\n<p>As a Groundwork Trust GWSC represents a strong partnership between government, business, foundations, community groups, and residents. Projects serve a common agenda and are designed to accomplish other goals, such as stewarding urban waterways, brown field reclamation, job training, environmental education, and developing future leaders through targeted youth leadership development. All projects and activities of Groundwork are carried out to leverage resources for residents to transform their own communities.</p>\n','Mission Statement','','inherit','closed','closed','','27-revision-v1','','','2017-06-04 15:36:00','2017-06-04 15:36:00','',27,'http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/27-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(317,8,'2017-06-04 15:41:01','2017-06-04 15:41:01','','about-sidebar','','publish','closed','closed','','about-sidebar','','','2017-06-04 15:41:01','2017-06-04 15:41:01','',0,'http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/fl-builder-template/about-sidebar',0,'fl-builder-template','',0),(318,8,'2017-06-04 15:41:22','2017-06-04 15:41:22','\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/mission-statement\">Mission Statement</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/why-fall-river-and-new-bedford\">Fall River &amp; New Bedford</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/history\">History</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/staff-and-board\">Staff &amp; Board</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/what-we-do/our-stories\">Our Stories</a></p>\n	<h2>MISSION STATEMENT</h2>\n<hr />\n<p>The mission of Groundwork Southcoast (GWSC) is to bring about the sustained regeneration, improvement and management of the physical environment by developing community-based partnerships that empower people, businesses and organizations to promote environmental, economic and social well-being.<br />\n&nbsp</p>\n<h2>OUR ROLE</h2>\n<hr />\n<p>GWSC is part of the <a href=\"http://groundworkusa.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Groundwork USA</strong></a> network of independent, not-for-profit, environmental organizations called Groundwork Trusts. Locally organized and controlled, Groundwork Trusts provide services focused on improving their communities environment, economy, and quality of life.</p>\n<p>As a Groundwork Trust GWSC represents a strong partnership between government, business, foundations, community groups, and residents. Projects serve a common agenda and are designed to accomplish other goals, such as stewarding urban waterways, brown field reclamation, job training, environmental education, and developing future leaders through targeted youth leadership development. All projects and activities of Groundwork are carried out to leverage resources for residents to transform their own communities.</p>\n','Mission Statement','','inherit','closed','closed','','27-revision-v1','','','2017-06-04 15:41:22','2017-06-04 15:41:22','',27,'http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/27-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(319,8,'2017-06-04 15:41:51','2017-06-04 15:41:51','\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/mission-statement\">Mission Statement</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/why-fall-river-and-new-bedford\">Fall River &amp; New Bedford</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/history\">History</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/staff-and-board\">Staff &amp; Board</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/what-we-do/our-stories\">Our Stories</a></p>\n	<h1>Why Fall River and New Bedford</h1>\n<hr>\n<p>GWSC is the only community-based environmental organization in either city whos organizing focuses on: youth, residents, and other stakeholders in a grassroots-fueled, neighborhood-scale planning and redevelopment initiative aimed at reclaiming vacant, contaminated, underutilized and/or under-maintained land and waterways for community benefit. This whats next? agenda is a strong suit of the Groundwork model and, as such, holds great potential for these two cities as well as building the next generation of organizers and social justice leaders while recognizing the key role that the voice of youth has to play in this work alongside of adult and other marginalized residents.</p>\n','Why Fall River and New Bedford','','inherit','closed','closed','','33-revision-v1','','','2017-06-04 15:41:51','2017-06-04 15:41:51','',33,'http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/33-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(320,8,'2017-06-04 16:28:33','2017-06-04 16:28:33','\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/mission-statement\">Mission Statement</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/why-fall-river-and-new-bedford\">Fall River &amp; New Bedford</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/history\">History</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/staff-and-board\">Staff &amp; Board</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/what-we-do/our-stories\">Our Stories</a></p>\n	<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">STAFF</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/06/P24-240x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"240\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n<h3><strong>Executive Director:</strong> Maura Ramsey</h3>\n<p>Maura has been with GWSC since March 2017. Sheis extremely passionate about furthering social, economic, racial, and environmental justice in our society through community focused leadership development. Prior to accepting the Executive Director position with GWSC, Maura worked at Mother\'s Out Front as the Massachusetts Lead Organizer, a non-profit that works to mobilize mothers, grandmothers and caregivers to have their voices heard as they advocate for a healthy climate for their children. She was also the Director of the South Street Youth Center, a non-profit located on the premises of a Boston Housing Authority development where she developed all programming and outreach to expand the youth center from onesmall drop-in program to a multi-service space that engaged, residents, neighbors, non-profits, city programs and state based stakeholder to respond to create the changes the community wanted.</p>\n	<hr />\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">BOARD</h1>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/06/me-300x226.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"281\" height=\"212\" /></p>\n<h3><strong>Chair:</strong> Mike Coughlin</h3>\n<p>Michael Coughlin, MS, has been a public health professional at the state and local level since 1992. He is the Outreach and Education Coordinator for Greater Fall River Partners for a Healthier Community and an Adjunct Instructor in Human Services and Psychology at Bristol Community College. He also serves as a Site Visitor for the national Public Health Accreditation Board. Michael retired as the Accreditation Manager in the Office of the Commissioner in the MA Department of Public Health (MDPH) in June 2015. He previously served as the Local Public Health Manager in the Emergency Preparedness Bureau at MDPH. He served as the Director of Health and Human Services for the City of Fall River, MA from 2004-2008.</p>\n<h3></h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Vice Chair:</strong> Ray Holberger</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3><strong>Secretary:</strong> Eric Andrade</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/uploads/2017/06/emerging-leader-head-shot-225x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></p>\n<h3><strong>Treasurer:</strong> Brian Pastori</h3>\n<p>Brian Pastori has lived in New Bedford since 2004 and is a founding board member of Groundwork SouthCoast. Brian is the Deputy Director of the Community Economic Development Center (CEDC). He has worked at the CEDC since 2005 promoting asset development, neighborhood pride, and skill building in New Bedford with a particular focus on the Acushnet Avenue Neighborhood. Brians work is guided by a commitment to social and economic justice with the goal of building toward equity for oppressed communities.</p>\n<h1></h1>\n	<hr />\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">MEMBERS</h1>\n<p>Jan De Silva</p>\n<p>Amy Blanchette</p>\n','Staff and Board','','inherit','closed','closed','','22-revision-v1','','','2017-06-04 16:28:33','2017-06-04 16:28:33','',22,'http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/22-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(321,4,'2017-06-04 16:59:23','2017-06-04 16:59:23','{\n    \"bb-theme::fl-nav-item-spacing\": {\n        \"value\": \"14\",\n        \"type\": \"theme_mod\",\n        \"user_id\": 4\n    },\n    \"bb-theme::fl-nav-font-size\": {\n        \"value\": \"16\",\n        \"type\": \"theme_mod\",\n        \"user_id\": 4\n    }\n}','','','trash','closed','closed','','8c046e43-e226-48ba-810d-c42b57a0b525','','','2017-06-04 16:59:23','2017-06-04 16:59:23','',0,'http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/8c046e43-e226-48ba-810d-c42b57a0b525',0,'customize_changeset','',0),(322,4,'2017-06-04 17:02:01','2017-06-04 17:02:01','{\n    \"custom_css[bb-theme]\": {\n        \"value\": \"/*\\nYou can add your own CSS here.\\n\\nClick the help icon above to learn more.\\n\\nright margin being over ridden by another source\\n*/\\n\\n/*.fl-page-header-container {\\n    padding-bottom: 0px\\n    padding-top: 20px;\\n    margin-left: 0px;\\n\\tmargin-bottom:0px;\\n    margin-right: 100px;\\n\\tpadding-left:20px;\\n\\tbackground: #333333;\\n}\\n*/\\n\\nli a {\\n    font-size: 50px;\\n}\\n\\n.addtoany_share_save_container {\\n    clear: both;\\n    padding-top: 25px;\\n    padding-bottom: 25px;\\n    text-align: center;\\n    margin-bottom: 0px;\\n}\\n\\n.fl-page-nav-col {\\ntext-align: right;\\nfloat: right;\\n}\\n\\n.tribe-icon-list{\\nfont-size:20px;\\n}\\n.tribe-icon-month{\\nfont-size:20px;\\n}\\n.tribe-icon-day{\\nfont-size:20px;\\n}\\n\\n/* ul#menu-main-menu li.header-font{\\nborder: 1px solid black;\\nbackground: brown;\\n} */\\n\\nul#menu-main-menu li.header-font a{\\nfont-size:25px;\\ncolor: #1fb25a;\\npa