6-04 19:38:25','',50,'http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/?p=355',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(356,8,'2017-06-04 19:45:41','2017-06-04 19:45:41','\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/mission-statement\">Mission Statement</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/why-fall-river-and-new-bedford\">Fall River &amp; New Bedford</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/history\">History</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/who-we-are/staff-and-board\">Staff &amp; Board</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/home-page/what-we-do/our-stories\">Our Stories</a></p>\n	<h2>Mission Statement</h2>\n<hr />\n<p>The mission of Groundwork Southcoast (GWSC) is to bring about the sustained regeneration, improvement and management of the physical environment by developing community-based partnerships that empower people, businesses and organizations to promote environmental, economic and social well-being.</p>\n<h2>Who We Are</h2>\n<hr />\n<p>GWSC is part of the <a href=\"http://groundworkusa.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Groundwork USA</strong></a> network of independent, not-for-profit, environmental organizations called Groundwork Trusts. Locally organized and controlled, Groundwork Trusts provide services focused on improving their communities environment, economy, and quality of life.</p>\n<p>As a Groundwork Trust GWSC represents a strong partnership between government, business, foundations, community groups, and residents. Projects serve a common agenda and are designed to accomplish other goals, such as stewarding urban waterways, brown field reclamation, job training, environmental education, and developing future leaders through targeted youth leadership development. All projects and activities of Groundwork are carried out to leverage resources for residents to transform their own communities.</p>\n<h2>What We do</h2>\n<hr />\n<p>GWSC works collaboratively to develop current and future leadership to steward urban waterways and brownfields in environmental justice communities in south eastern Massachusetts.</p>\n','Mission Statement','','inherit','closed','closed','','27-revision-v1','','','2017-06-04 19:45:41','2017-06-04 19:45:41','',27,'http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/27-revision-v1',0,'revision','',0),(357,8,'2017-06-04 19:53:59','2017-06-04 19:53:59','\n<h1>Thank you for supporting Groundwork Southcoast!</h1>\n<p>Help support our programming in 2017.</p>\n<p>Your gift to Groundwork Southcoast helps us further our mission to establish and promote environmental equity by increasing access to safe and healthy outdoor spaces, providing local youth with summerjobs, and building a strong successful support for the Southcoast of Massachusetts for years to come.</p>\n<p><em>All donations are tax deductible.</em></p>\n<p><em>Continue to our secure donation page.</em></p>\n			<a href=\"UpDateLinkWithSwipeAccount.com\" target=\"_blank\" role=\"button\">\n						Donate\n					</a>\n<h1>Groundwork Southcoast\'s Wish List</h1>\n<p>Have items laying around? Below is a list of items that are most needed by our programs.</p>\n<p>Contact mramsey<a href=\"mailto:katelyn@groundworkmke.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">@groundworksouthcoast.org</a> to arrange a wish list donation!</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>Green Team / Young Farmer Needs</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Van (to transport Green Team members)</li>\n<li>Reusable Water Bottles</li>\n<li>Non-Perishable Snacks (granola bars, fruit cups, juice boxes, etc.)</li>\n<li>Outerwear (fleece sweatshirts, jackets, etc.)</li>\n<li>Ponchos/Rain Coats</li>\n<li>Meeting space for youth and staff in the Flint neighborhood in Fall River</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Beautification Needs</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Shovels</li>\n<li>Trowels</li>\n<li>weeding claws</li>\n<li>Rakes</li>\n<li>watering cans</li>\n<li>hose</li>\n<li>Garden 