INSERT INTO `wp_rg_incomplete_submissions` VALUES ('2707f810993b48a68a09687392271aa5','mramsey@groundworksouthcoast.org',1,'2017-05-31 15:56:48','73.61.9.129','http://groundworksouth.48in48sites.org/branding-questionnaire','{\"submitted_values\":{\"1\":\"\",\"2\":\"\",\"3\":\"\",\"4\":\"Groundwork Southcoast\",\"5\":\"Groundwork Southcoast\",\"33\":\"To bring about the sustained regeneration, improvement, and management of the physical environment by developing community-based partnerships that empower people, businesses, and organizations to promote environmental, economic, and social well-being.\",\"34\":\"\\\"changing places; changing lives\\\"\",\"6\":\"(508) 974-3535\",\"7\":{\"7.1\":\"1285 Acushnet Avenue\",\"7.2\":\"\",\"7.3\":\"New Bedford\",\"7.4\":\"\",\"7.5\":\"02746-2020\",\"7.6\":\"United States\",\"7_copy_values_activated\":false},\"8\":\"\",\"9\":\"\",\"11\":\"To work to steward and create physical spaces in Fall River and New Bedford and by so doing foster stewardship of the communities in which these spaces exist. By so doing, we seek to have physical impacts also foster socioeconomic and health impacts, cultivate community based leadership, and positive youth development. This targets brownfields, urban waterways and other spaces in environmental justice communities. GWSC is uniquely additive to the work in each city with a focus on building community based justice.\",\"10\":\"We have just launched, but we will have a summer youth employment program called \\\"the Green team\\\" and we are focused on working across sectors that touch the communities we serve: non-profits, schools, government, business and residents. By working collaboratively, we seek  to add capacity to the great work and ideas already in place as well as to augment these ideas as our organization grows in scope. We are also focused on deep grassroots organizing to build marginalized community voice and buy-in on current and future stewardship projects. \\r\\nAs our organization continues to grow in scope, we plan to continue to focus on adding programming that will work towards positive youth development.\",\"12\":\"We work in outdoor spaces and on projects that relate to the environment to build community buy-in and connection\\/ usage to these spaces. We work to develop community leadership and youth development. We create healthy spaces and in that process empower the communities surrounding these spaces.\",\"13\":\"We change the urban landscape and empower the communities that reside near these landscapes.\",\"14\":\"Empower people to change their communities\",\"15\":\"Groundwork Southcoast (GWSC) is 9 years in the making. Dedicated people in both Fall River and New Bedford learned about Groundwork USA\'s model and have been steadily working to make a Southcoast trust a reality. GWSC is a trust in the national network of 23 trusts across the U.S.  that currently make up Groundwork USA. Each trust is started by communities applying to start a trust. Starting GWSC has been the collaborative effort of the cities of Fall River and New Bedford as well as another trust: Groundwork Lawrence. The vision for a Groundwork Southcoast emerged from the belief that while the two cities are not unique in their deficits, their pool of assets represents a foundation upon which authentic community stewardship and engagement, as well as land and waterway transformation, can be built. Governance Board members from both communities are clear that a shared Groundwork presence is the best means for translating their challenges, needs and assets into high-quality impact and growth of opportunity. \\r\\n\\r\\nAs advocates in both cities were building momentum to advocate for GWSC, the National Park Service and Groundwork USA revisited the idea and allocated funding toward exploration of a regional \\u201cGroundwork Massachusetts\\u201d concept. This began in 2013 as a result of having received increasing interest in the Groundwork model from multiple Gateway Cities (former industrial mill cities in MA, where economic decline is prevalent as economies and industry have changed across the Commonwealth), Supported by leadership of Executive Directors at Groundwork Lawrence (GWL) and Groundwork Somerville (GWS), began to explore possible legal and organizational structures for a statewide entity. Essentially, any Groundwork presence in a Massachusetts \\u201cGateway City\\u201d would be apart of a vision for a regional entity supporting the needs for community revitalization and capacity building on the southern coast of Massachusetts as well as potentially other parts of the state in the future.\",\"16\":\"It indicates the region in which the trust exists as apart of the USA Groundwork network\",\"17\":\"By building investment in outdoor spaces, we can build connection and investment in and by the communities in which these spaces exist. \\r\\nInviting, empowering, successful,\",\"18\":\"environmental justice, community-based, collaborative, empowering, leadership development, strategic change\",\"19\":\"exclusive, inaccessible, unreliable\",\"20\":\"Making the love of nature accessible for everyone and using the power of this fuel social, economic and racial justice; \\r\\nyouth enthusiasm when learning about new things in the natural world\",\"21\":\"Dolores Huerta? \\r\\nShe worked on both physical spaces and social justice for her community.  She worked with farm laborers who were often overlooked in society as are most environmental justice communities today and while people often know Cesar Chavez more than Dolores Huerta, the communities in which she directly worked have immense respect for her and her contributions to their wellbeing.\",\"22\":\"a beaver- we see them in the middle of the city in one of the urban spaces where they work. They may be small, but their have huge positive impacts in the environment in which they industriously work\",\"32\":\"ACE- Alternatives for Community and the Environment; also work i